      • withCertificateBundle

        public ConsumerBuilder withCertificateBundle(java.lang.String verifyCertBundle)

        Set the certificate bundle chain to be used at build() when creating Consumer instance.

        Parameters:
        verifyCertBundle - CA Bundle chain certificates. This string shall be either the certificates themselves or a path to a CA bundle file containing those certificates. The CA bundle is used to validate that the certificate of the authentication server being connected to was signed by a valid authority. If set to an empty string, the server certificate will not be validated.
        Returns:
        this ConsumerBuilder instance

      • withExtraConfigs

        public ConsumerBuilder withExtraConfigs(java.util.Properties extraConfigs)

        Set the extraConfigs value to be used at build() when creating Consumer instance

        Parameters:
        extraConfigs - Dictionary of key/value pairs containing any custom configuration settings which should be sent to the streaming service when a consumer is created. Examples of key/value pairs are: ("auto.offset.reset", "latest"); ("request.timeout.ms", 30000) and ("session.timeout.ms", 10000).
        Returns:
        this ConsumerBuilder instance

      • build

        public Consumer build()
               throws TemporaryError

        Build a Channel object using the previously set parameters and expose it as a Consumer object.

        Returns:
        a Consumer object which only exposes the Channel consume related methods, e.g.: Channel.create(), Channel.subscribe(List), Channel.subscriptions(), Channel.consume(), Channel.commit(), Channel.run(ConsumerRecordProcessor, List, int), Channel.delete(), Channel.stop() and Channel.close()
        Throws:
        TemporaryError - if Channel http client request object failed to be created.
